00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:01,823
<i><b>You covered what she owed with
your own money, didn't you?</b></i>

194
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,320
<i><b>Because that's above
and beyond...</b></i>

195
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,777
<i><b>We can talk about
how awesome I am later.</b></i>

196
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:05,860
<i><b>Right now,
I need to make sure</b></i>

197
00:08:05,944 --> 00:08:07,571
<i><b>that Sofia's rent
is paid by 10:00.</b></i>

198
00:08:11,408 --> 00:08:13,081
<i><b>Louis, can I talk to you?</b></i>

199
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,540
<i><b>Of course.</b></i>

200
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:17,839
<i><b>I... I don't even know what to do.
My hands are shaking.</b></i>

201
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,211
<i><b>Rachel, what's going on?</b></i>

202
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,585
<i><b>I'm not getting into the Bar.</b></i>

203
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:22,920
<i><b>What? That's ridiculous.</b></i>

204
00:08:23,003 --> 00:08:24,220
<i><b>Read this.</b></i>

205
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:26,256
<i><b>Let's see this.</b></i>

206
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:27,556
<i><b>"After careful review
of your application,</b></i>

207
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:28,679
<i><b>"the character
and fitness committee</b></i>

208
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,180
<i><b>"will not be granting you
an interview"?</b></i>

209
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,352
<i><b>This is bullshit.
I know.</b></i>

210
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:32,805
<i><b>Because I knew I was going
to have to defend myself,</b></i>

211
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,487
<i><b>but I didn't think
I wasn't even going to</b></i>

212
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,187
<i><b>have the chance
to defend myself.</b></i>

213
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:38,109
<i><b>Okay. Calm down.
How can I calm down?</b></i>

214
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:39,824
<i><b>This is exactly
what my dad was afraid of.</b></i>

215
00:08:39,894 --> 00:08:42,488
<i><b>He said that they'd hold my
relationship with Mike against me.</b></i>

216
00:08:42,564 --> 00:08:43,884
<i><b>You don't know
this is about Mike.</b></i>

217
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:45,984
<i><b>Of course,
it's about Mike. What...</b></i>

218
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:48,244
<i><b>What else would it be about?</b></i>

219
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:50,321
<i><b>It could be a mix-up,
some kind of clerical error.</b></i>

220
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:52,247
<i><b>You could have filled out
the paperwork wrong.</b></i>

221
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:54,167
<i><b>I went over it 10 times.</b></i>

222
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:56,374
<i><b>Rachel, there is
an explanation for this</b></i>

223
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:57,545
<i><b>and I'm going to get
to the bottom of it.</b></i>

224
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,463
<i><b>You don't know that.
Look at me.</b></i>

225
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:03,631
<i><b>I promise you will
get your interview. Okay?</b></i>

226
00:09:04,335 --> 00:09:05,461
<i><b>Okay.</b></i>

227
00:09:12,177 --> 00:09:13,679
<i><b>Harvey, we have a problem.</b></i>

228
00:09:13,762 --> 00:09:14,934
<i><b>What is it?</b></i>

229
00:09:16,473 --> 00:09:17,473
<i><b>This is about Mike.</b></i>

230
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:18,732
<i><b>Of course it's about Mike.
That's why I came here</b></i>

231
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:20,310
<i><b>the second
Rachel left my office.</b></i>

232
00:09:20,435 --> 00:09:22,233
<i><b>What did you tell Rachel?
What do you think I told her?</b></i>

233
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:23,780
<i><b>I told her that it must be
some kind of mistake.</b></i>

234
00:09:23,855 --> 00:09:24,902
<i><b>But you and I
both know it's not,</b></i>

235
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:26,028
<i><b>which means
you need to fix this.</b></i>

236
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:28,235
<i><b>Yeah, I do need to fix it
and I will.</b></i>

237
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:30,495
<i><b>But normally,</b></i>

238
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,743
<i><b>instead of coming to me,
you'd go full steam ahead</b></i>

239
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:35,416
<i><b>and do something that makes the
situation significantly worse.</b></i>

240
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:36,994
<i><b>Possibly.
What are you getting at?</b></i>

241
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,037
<i><b>Why did you come to me?</b></i>

242
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,666
<i><b>Because we said
we'd run this firm together.</b></i>

243
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:45,093
<i><b>And if we're gonna do that, then
I have to be honest with myself</b></i>

244
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:46,636
<i><b>about what I'm good at
and what you're good at.</b></i>

245
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:49,031
<i><b>And you know I'm better at this
kind of thing than you are.</b></i>

246
00:09:49,339 --> 00:09:50,511
<i><b>I do.</b></i>

247
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,434
<i><b>Louis, that shows real growth.
Thank you, Harvey.</b></i>

248
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:54,511
<i><b>And it shows growth
on your part</b></i>

249
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:58,064
<i><b>not to make light of the fact that
I just admitted something that was</b></i>

250
00:09:58,139 --> 00:09:59,812
<i><b>very difficult
for me to admit.</b></i>

251
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:02,106
<i><b>You mean that I'm better
at everything than you.</b></i>

252
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:05,064
<i><b>That's not what I said. Too bad.
Because it's what I heard.</b></i>

253
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,065
<i><b>Okay.
Harvey, seriously.</b></i>

254
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:08,616
<i><b>This is not about
you having fun with me.</b></i>

255
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:09,988
<i><b>This is about Rachel.</b></i>

256
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:14,239
<i><b>I know it is. And if I weren't confident
that I could take care of it,</b></i>

257
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:16,040
<i><b>I wouldn't be giving you
a hard time</b></i>

258
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:18,039
<i><b>for admitting how much better
I am at everything than you.</b></i>

259
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:19,961
<i><b>God damn it.
Sorry, Louis.</b></i>

260
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:21,583
<i><b>Got to go be
better at something.</b></i>

261
00:10:21,663 --> 00:10:22,710
<i><b>See you later.</b></i>

262
00:10:31,923 --> 00:10:33,015
<i><b>Can I help you?</b></i>

263
00:10:33,091 --> 00:10:34,684
<i><b>Yes, you can.
My name is Mike Ross.</b></i>

264
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,978
<i><b>I'm here on behalf
of Sofia Price.</b></i>

265
00:10:37,053 --> 00:10:39,397
<i><b>And this is every dime of
rent she owes your client.</b></i>

266
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:41,770
<i><b>And why exactly
are you bringing that to me?</b></i>

267
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:43,397
<i><b>Because you're an attorney,
not a landlord.</b></i>

268
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:45,899
<i><b>And I don't want there
to be any misunderstandings.</b></i>

269
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:48,277
<i><b>What I understand
is that it's 10:18,</b></i>

270
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,108
<i><b>and your client
had until 10:00.</b></i>

271
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:51,488
<i><b>You have got to be
shitting me.</b></i>

272
00:10:51,568 --> 00:10:52,911
<i><b>I most certainly am not.</b></i>

273
00:10:52,986 --> 00:10:54,533
<i><b>And maybe your client
should have thought of that</b></i>

274
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,990
<i><b>before not paying
her rent all those months.</b></i>

275
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,325
<i><b>You think I don't know
what's going on here?</b></i>

276
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:00,285
<i><b>You're trying to get her out so
that you can get this place out</b></i>

277
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:02,666
<i><b>from under rent control. But I'm not
gonna let you get away with it.</b></i>

278
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:04,705
<i><b>No, what's going on here
is that my client is sick</b></i>

279
00:11:04,747 --> 00:11:08,297
<i><b>of having a troublemaker who
doesn't pay her rent as a tenant.</b></i>

280
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:09,376
<i><b>Listen to me.</b></i>

281
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:12,389
<i><b>You cannot evict her now.
Her son is in the hospital.</b></i>

282
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:13,760
<i><b>I have a job to do.</b></i>

283
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,844
<i><b>Now, I am sorry
about your client's son.</b></i>

284
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:20,430
<i><b>But the court was very clear, and
there's nothing more that I can do.</b></i>

285
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:28,025
<i><b>Mike.
What happened?</b></i>

286
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,572
<i><b>I got there
18 minutes late.</b></i>

287
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:31,767
<i><b>What does that matter? You
had three months back rent.</b></i>

288
00:11:31,816 --> 00:11:33,409
<i><b>They want to kick her out
to get out of rent control.</b></i>

289
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:34,531
<i><b>And now that
we've missed the deadline,</b></i>

290
00:11:34,611 --> 00:11:35,863
<i><b>there's nothing
we can do about it.</b></i>

291
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,367
<i><b>Wrong. There is.</b></i>

292
00:11:37,739 --> 00:11:39,207
<i><b>I got to thinking. Why would
they be in such a hurry</b></i>

293
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:41,563
<i><b>to evict somebody who can
actually come up with the money?</b></i>

294
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:43,499
<i><b>They're not just
trying to get her out,</b></i>

295
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:44,670
<i><b>they're trying to
get everyone out.</b></i>

296
00:11:44,746 --> 00:11:45,963
<i><b>Exactly.</b></i>

297
00:11:46,289 --> 00:11:47,461
<i><b>They're going to demolish
that whole building.</b></i>

298
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:48,792
<i><b>I was over there last night.</b></i>

299
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:49,876
<i><b>The workers
were already there.</b></i>

300
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:51,381
<i><b>Which means
they've already started.</b></i>

301
00:11:51,461 --> 00:11:53,680
<i><b>I get it. You want to hit
them with a countersuit.</b></i>

302
00:11:53,755 --> 00:11:54,847
<i><b>I want to nail their asses
to the wall.</b></i>

303
00:11:54,923 --> 00:11:56,015
<i><b>Now, you guys
get to work on the suit.</b></i>

304
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,091
<i><b>I'm going
to go talk to Nathan</b></i>

305
00:11:57,175 --> 00:11:59,473
<i><b>about stopping Sofia's eviction
from happening in the meantime.</b></i>

306
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:00,769
<i><b>Mike.</b></i>

307
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:04,641
<i><b>You don't need to go to Nathan.
I can handle this.</b></i>

308
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:06,738
<i><b>Listen, I appreciate that, but...
I get it.</b></i>

309
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:08,356
<i><b>I shit the bed the other day.</b></i>

310
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:09,858
<i><b>Oliver.
Look, Mike.</b></i>

311
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:12,236
<i><b>I admit, sometimes
I get flustered in court.</b></i>

312
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:14,280
<i><b>But the law is clear on this.
It's a layup.</b></i>

313
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:17,454
<i><b>If we have a pending lawsuit, it puts
an automatic hold on the eviction.</b></i>

314
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:19,201
<i><b>I'm telling you,
I can handle this.</b></i>

315
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,328
<i><b>Please, let me make up
for the other day.</b></i>

316
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:24,669
<i><b>Then what are you
waiting for?</b></i>

317
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:27,919
<i><b>Get your ass down to court and let
me know as soon as it's done.</b></i>

318
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:37,445
<i><b>All right, Benjamin.
Playtime's over.</b></i>

319
00:12:37,507 --> 00:12:39,180
<i><b>What the hell did you do
to my computer?</b></i>

320
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,887
<i><b>I didn't do anything to it, other
than increase its performance.</b></i>

321
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:43,472
<i><b>If that's your idea
of increasing performance,</b></i>

322
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:45,101
<i><b>then you ought to
rethink your career.</b></i>

323
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:46,433
<i><b>Because that thing
has crashed more times</b></i>

324
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:49,110
<i><b>than Mel Gibson on his way
home from a Saturday night.</b></i>

325
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:51,691
<i><b>Wait a second.
Are you smiling?</b></i>

326
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:53,777
<i><b>Of course not. You're yelling at me.
Why would I be smiling?</b></i>

327
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:55,233
<i><b>Don't bullshit
a bullshitter, Benjamin.</b></i>

328
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,676
<i><b>You're up to something. And you
better come clean right now.</b></i>

329
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,199
<i><b>Okay.</b></i>

330
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:01,702
<i><b>I was hoping to do this in a
more formal environment. But...</b></i>

331
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,413
<i><b>Allow me to introduce
The Donna.</b></i>

332
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:10,169
<i><b>What the hell is that?</b></i>

333
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:11,841
<i><b>It's a digital version
of you,</b></i>

334
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,793
<i><b>with approximately
10,000 of your best quotes,</b></i>

335
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:17,301
<i><b>witticisms and zingers packed into
five gigahertz of computing power.</b></i>

336
00:13:17,672 --> 00:13:19,470
<i><b>That's why you've been
personally updating my computer</b></i>

337
00:13:19,549 --> 00:13:20,766
<i><b>and nobody else's?</b></i>

338
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:21,809
<i><b>Yes. I've been
secretly recording you</b></i>

339
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:23,056
<i><b>for the better part
of two years.</b></i>

340
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:24,479
<i><b>Two years?</b></i>

341
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:26,681
<i><b>Why me?</b></i>

342
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,141
<i><b>Because everyone
always wishes they could</b></i>

343
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,521
<i><b>say the right thing
at the right time.</b></i>

344
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,680
<i><b>And you are the one woman in the universe
who says the right thing every time.</b></i>

345
00:13:32,687 --> 00:13:34,167
<i><b>Not to mention
you are without a doubt</b></i>

346
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:36,670
<i><b>the most amazing legal secretary
in the history of everything.</b></i>

347
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:40,161
<i><b>Benjamin, that's the sweetest
thing anyone's ever said to me.</b></i>

348
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:42,330
<i><b>Okay, but you said it
about yourself two weeks ago.</b></i>

349
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:44,328
<i><b>That I did.
In that case,</b></i>

350
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:46,334
<i><b>Donna Paulsen, I wasn't
going to ask you this</b></i>

351
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:47,877
<i><b>for another few weeks,
but how would you feel</b></i>

352
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:51,001
<i><b>about pursuing this with me
as a business opportunity?</b></i>

353
00:13:52,707 --> 00:13:54,084
<i><b>Let me think about it.</b></i>

354
00:13:54,459 --> 00:13:56,632
<i><b>But first, let me borrow
that thing for a few days.</b></i>

355
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:07,267
<i><b>You want to tell me
why you're playing games</b></i>

356
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:09,975
<i><b>with my associate's
admission to the Bar?</b></i>

357
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:12,352
<i><b>You're Harvey Specter.</b></i>

358
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:13,652
<i><b>In the flesh. And if I
don't walk out of here</b></i>

359
00:14:13,728 --> 00:14:15,071
<i><b>with an appointment
in my hand,</b></i>

360
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:16,443
<i><b>you're going to find out
what that means.</b></i>

361
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,945
<i><b>Because Rachel Zane
deserves to make her case.</b></i>

362
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,110
<i><b>Rachel Zane.</b></i>

363
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:22,787
<i><b>This is clearly
a scheduling error.</b></i>

364
00:14:22,904 --> 00:14:23,951
<i><b>I'm sorry.</b></i>

365
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:27,417
<i><b>I will, uh, set her interview
for two weeks from today.</b></i>

366
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:30,172
<i><b>I'd say thank you, but you should
have done that in the first place.</b></i>

367
00:14:30,745 --> 00:14:32,385
<i><b>I don't think
she's going to pass, though.</b></i>

368
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:35,248
<i><b>What did you say?</b></i>

369
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,338
<i><b>I just thought
you should know</b></i>

370
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:38,937
<i><b>the vote has to be unanimous among
the members of the committee.</b></i>

371
00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:42,966
<i><b>And I have a sense that at
least one isn't gonna say yes.</b></i>

372
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,801
<i><b>Well, you could have
just rejected her.</b></i>

373
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,324
<i><b>But you went to the trouble to
get me down here, so get to it.</b></i>

374
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,439
<i><b>Well, I'm just saying,</b></i>

375
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:54,352
<i><b>that if someone were to, say,</b></i>

376
00:14:55,478 --> 00:14:57,731
<i><b>sue my biggest competitor
for enough money</b></i>

377
00:14:57,814 --> 00:14:59,782
<i><b>so that their stock price
plummets,</b></i>

378
00:15:00,608 --> 00:15:03,487
<i><b>perhaps Miss Zane's chances would
take a turn for the better.</b></i>

379
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:04,661
<i><b>Let me get this straight.</b></i>

380
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:06,205
<i><b>You're on
the Ethics Committee</b></i>

381
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,248
<i><b>and you're asking me
to do something illegal.</b></i>

382
00:15:08,366 --> 00:15:11,040
<i><b>It's not illegal if you can find
